evidence:
The site is a UX copy branch, not a visibility gate, exactly as F7 characterizes — and it now reads through the navigation contract. In apps/mobile/src/app/(app)/mentor-memory.tsx the accommodation badge (testID="accommodation-badge") is already rendered; inside it, lines 501-508 conditionally append a sub-Text:

  {!isOwnerSelf ? (
    <Text testID="accommodation-set-by-parent" ...>
      {t('session.mentorMemory.accommodation.setByParent')}
    </Text>
  ) : null}

`isOwnerSelf` is sourced from the contract at line 68: `const isOwnerSelf = navigationContract.gates.sessionIsOwner;` (useNavigationContract() at line 61). The gate is defined in apps/mobile/src/lib/navigation-contract.ts:364 — `sessionIsOwner: ownerRole && !context.isParentProxy`. The i18n key exists (src/i18n/locales/en.json:383 "session.mentorMemory.accommodation.setByParent": "Set by your parent in their settings.") and is fully translated across locales. Branch toggles only a secondary attribution line within an already-visible badge — confirms "copy branching, not visibility gate." No raw `role==='owner'` check remains at this site. (The earlier moved line numbers 469→501 from C17 match.)
